reviewText: So not a whole lot of people would remember this but this was a great film, but the film was introduced through a Jim Henson Hour deal. It had a lot of great shorts and the making of dog city (shown by dogs). It was great. My sister got me this when I was in the hospital and was stoked and brought a smile. The movie is great, but not having behind the scenes, bean bunny trailers, kermit going crazy trying to find the reel to the film, and a robot guy or whatever is just highly disappointed. But shouldn't let it stop you from seeing this.
summary: Highly disappointed for only the movie.
Title: N/A

reviewText: Like many have said, the first half and ending halfs of this Jim Henson Hour episode have been edited out and it's basically just the Dog City film part of The Jim Henson Hour. I kind of hesitated in wanting to buy it because of that but still, where else can you get The Jim Henson Hour episodes legally? So I bought the DVD, waiting and expecting a bad menu or something and suddenly I hear The Jim Henson Hour theme playing and that just brought a smile to my face. And also the behind the scenes photo gallery featuring a late Jim Henson on the set of Dog City looking at everything in a classic thinking pose. Awesome special feature. But still I yearn for The Jim Henson Hour complete series. This is good for an economic priced DVD but there should be a complete series for us collectors / Jim Henson Muppet fans know what I mean? But other then that, the film segment of the episode is uncut and uncensored. Buggy Them's Machine Gun and All! :) Nice an PG! Or what Buggy Them would say "Senseless Violence, just the way I love it" lol But what's amazing about this was, it was when The Jim Henson Company was slightly going more towards a satirical view within the later work which of course would bring us one of the greatest satirical shows ever "Dinosaurs" which was Jim Henson's original idea but wasn't made until a year after his passing. Anyway, I give it 4, I would give it 5 but it's mainly because it's cut.
summary: We need More Jim Henson Hour DVDs

reviewText: Since The Muppets got bought by Disney, certain specials that featured Kermit the Frog had Kermit footage cut out of them a little less enjoyable...but for some reason, they were able to keep Rowlf the Dog uncut from this film noir comedy special and the story itself is a hoot. It's a must have for Muppet fans not to mention Rowlf fans
